#. Tag: title
#: storage_lvm.xml:585
#, no-c-format
msgid "Thinly Provisioned Logical Volumes"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_lvm.xml:586
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An LVM logical volume can optionally be thinly provisioned. Thin "
"provisioning allows you to create logical volumes with sizes that overbook "
"the available free space. You create a thin pool that contains unused space "
"reserved for use with an arbitrary number of thin volumes. A thin volume is "
"created as a sparse volume and space is allocated from a thin pool as "
"needed. The thin pool can be expanded dynamically when needed for cost-"
"effective allocation of storage space. Thinly provisioned volumes also "
"support snapshots which can be managed with Snapper&mdash;see <xref linkend="
"\"cha.snapper\"/> for more information."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_lvm.xml:597
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To set up a thinly provisioned logical volume, proceed as described in <xref "
"linkend=\"pro.lvm.lv\"/>. When it comes to choosing the volume type, do not "
"choose <guimenu>Normal Volume</guimenu>, but rather <guimenu>Thin Volume</"
"guimenu> or <guimenu>Thin Pool</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

