"accepted upstream."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_lvm.xml:1632
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Dynamic Aggregation of LVM Metadata via <systemitem class=\"daemon"
"\">lvmetad</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_lvm.xml:1633
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Most LVM commands require an accurate view of the LVM metadata stored on the "
"disk devices in the system. With the current LVM design, if this information "
"is not available, LVM must scan all the physical disk devices in the system. "
"This requires a significant amount of I/O operations in systems that have "
"many disks. In case a disk fails to respond, LVM commands might run into a "
"timeout while waiting for the disk."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_lvm.xml:1641
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Dynamic aggregation of LVM metadata via <systemitem class=\"daemon"
"\">lvmetad</systemitem> provides a solution for this problem. The purpose of "
"the <systemitem class=\"daemon\">lvmetad</systemitem> daemon is to eliminate "
"the need for this scanning by dynamically aggregating metadata information "
"each time the status of a device changes. These events are signaled to "
"<systemitem class=\"daemon\">lvmetad</systemitem> by udev rules. If the "
"daemon is not running, LVM performs a scan as it normally would do."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_lvm.xml:1651
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This feature is enabled by default. In case it is disabled on your system, "
"proceed as follows to enable it:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_lvm.xml:1662
#, no-c-format
msgid "Stop the <systemitem class=\"daemon\">lvmetad</systemitem> daemon:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_lvm.xml:1665
#, no-c-format
msgid "sudo systemctl stop lvm2-lvmetad"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_lvm.xml:1668
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Edit <filename>/etc/lvm/lvm.conf</filename> and set <literal>use_lvmetad</"
"literal> to <literal>1</literal>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_lvm.xml:1672
#, no-c-format
msgid "use_lvmetad = 1"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_lvm.xml:1675
#, no-c-format
msgid "Restart the <systemitem class=\"daemon\">lvmetad</systemitem> daemon:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_lvm.xml:1678
#, no-c-format
msgid "sudo systemctl start lvm2-lvmetad"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_lvm.xml:1684
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using LVM Cache Volumes"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_lvm.xml:1685
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"LVM supports the use of fast block devices (such as an SSD device) as write-"
"back or write-through caches for large slower block devices. The cache "
"logical volume type uses a small and fast LV to improve the performance of a "
"large and slow LV."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_lvm.xml:1691
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To set up LVM caching, you need to create two logical volumes on the caching "
"device. A large one is used for the caching itself, a smaller volume is used "
"to store the caching metadata. These two volumes need to be part of the same "
"volume group as the original volume. When these volumes are created, they "
"need to be converted into a cache pool which needs to be attached to the "
"original volume:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_lvm.xml:1700
#, no-c-format
msgid "Setting up a Cached Logical Volume"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_lvm.xml:1702
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create the original volume (on a slow device) if not already existing."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_lvm.xml:1707
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Add the physical volume (from a fast device) to the same volume group the "
"original volume is part of and create the cache data volume on the physical "
"volume."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_lvm.xml:1714
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create the cache metadata volume. The size should be 1/1000 of the size of "
"the cache data volume, with a minimum size of 8 MB."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_lvm.xml:1720
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Combine the cache data volume and metadata volume into a cache pool volume:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_lvm.xml:1724
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"lvconvert --type cache-pool --poolmetadata <replaceable>volume_group/"
"metadata_volume</replaceable> <replaceable>volume_group/caching_volume</"
"replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_lvm.xml:1727
#, no-c-format
msgid "Attach the cache pool to the original volume:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_lvm.xml:1730
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"lvconvert --type cache --cachepool <replaceable>volume_group/caching_volume</"
"replaceable> <replaceable>volume_group/original_volume</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_lvm.xml:1733
